14/08/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The overwhelming majority of the public expects the new VMRO-DPMNE-led cabinet to focus on the economy, according to a poll released at the weekend. 
The survey, by the Centre for Research and Policy, found that 84.2 per cent of respondents expect measures to improve the economic situation, 32.6 per cent expect new jobs and 16.8 per cent expect a reduction in poverty. 
Only 1.5 per cent of those polled mentioned interethnic relations. 
(Vecer, MRT - 12/08/06)
